King Charles III "simply won't have time" for a meeting with Prince Harry, prior to his Coronation Day, a source has stated. The friend of the King recently told The Daily Beast: "Charles adores Harry and wants him to be there. "But he has a Coronation to organise." Prince Harry has reportedly requested to hold a meeting with his father before he, and Meghan Markle, accept their invite to the event on May 6. The 38-year-old wants to clear the air with not only his father but also his elder brother, before he sets about flying over to the UK, from his home in the US. FOLLOW BELOW FOR OUR LATEST ROYAL UPDATES...